Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Rivers State Governor Nyesom Wike has branded the general election, especially the presidential poll, a fight-to-finish between the  Peoples Democratic Party(PDP) in the state  and  ”those who  hate Rivers State.” Recalling that the PDP has never lost any election in the state, Wike assured the people that the state’s interest will prevail as the ruling party would win the governorship, and national and House of Assembly elections. He spoke yesterday at the Local Government Campaign Council inauguration of the state   PDP at the Felix Obuah Pavilion, Omoku in Ogba-Egbema-Ndoni Local Government Area (ONELGA). Rivers State Governor Nyesom Wike has branded the general election, especially the presidential poll, a fight-to-finish between the  Peoples Democratic Party(PDP) in the state  and  ”those who  hate Rivers State.” Recalling that the PDP has never lost any election in the state, Wike assured the people that the state’s interest will prevail as the ruling party would win the governorship, and national and House of Assembly elections. He spoke yesterday at the Local Government Campaign Council inauguration of the state   PDP at the Felix Obuah Pavilion, Omoku in Ogba-Egbema-Ndoni Local Government Area (ONELGA). The governor described the forthcoming elections as a watershed that would decide the fate of those, working against the interest of the state. He told the gathering that the leaders of the party would approach voters and brief them on the direction of the state for the presidential election which holds February 25.